        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:103:2",
        "text": [
          " لَا يُصِيبُ قَرْيَةً عَذَابٌ وَ فِيهَا سَبْعَةٌ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, from Abu Hamza, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘A town would not be hit by a Punishment while there are seven from the <span class=\"iTxt\">Momineen</span> therein’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ib Muhammad from ibn Mahbub from ‘Abd Allah ibn Sinan from abu Hamza from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “A town in which seven believers live remains safe from torment.” "
          ]
        }
      },
